HEADWORD: Sawtooth
<hw>Saw"tooth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An arctic seal (<spn>Lobodon carcinophaga</spn>), having the molars
serrated; -- called also <altname>crab-eating seal</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

